§ 157.033 HB HIGHWAY BUSINESS DISTRICT.
(A) Intent. This district is intended to provide for commercial areas to be located on highways and major
thoroughfares in the community. The uses allowed in this district are primarily retail trade or service
establishments dependent on the traffic volume or transportation access characteristics of highways and
major thoroughfares or high intensity commercial uses located on high traffic routes to avoid conflict with
less intense land uses. Although this district is expressly designed for location along major thoroughfares it is
intended that these uses should be clustered in nodes as much as possible to limit the number of highway
access points and prevent undesirable strip development.
